cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.MA 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the development and evaluation of a vehicular networking testbed for V2X communication. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the firmware operating on the network devices and the system performance evaluation. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper deals with the design and implementation of a real-world system for intelligent transportation. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possible category as the paper may touch upon security issues related to V2X communication. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a less likely category, but the paper may touch upon the coordination and communication between multiple agents (vehicles) in the V2X network.
